{"source_key":"sha256-852da461b9759bc2736926d9891eb9a3","record_index":10049,"record_hash":"sha256:8c97e09728d0a357e4e5e8bad81b9fb073da2e639a612e9184a639860cc7ef9a","timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:45:36.294Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"Mostly good shape, but I’d simplify the mental model.\\n\\nPick this:\\n\\n```bash\\nbut agent sessions [branch <branch> | review <review> | change <change>] [--limit N]\\nbut agent timeline <session-id> [--limit N]\\nbut agent records <session-id> --turn <turn-id> [--from start|end|<index>] [--limit N]\\n```\\n\\nDrop `agentlog`. Agents don’t care that it’s a log; they care that it’s agent context. `but agent ...` is easier to teach and leaves room for future commands.\\n\\n**Main recommendation**\\n\\nMerge `timeline` and `records` behavior a little via defaults:\\n\\n```bash\\nbut agent show <session-id> [--limit N]\\nbut agent show <session-id> --turn <turn-id> [--from start|end|<index>] [--limit N]\\n```\\n\\nWhy: the workflow becomes:\\n\\n1. Find sessions.\\n2. Show session.\\n3. Drill into a turn if needed.\\n\\nThat’s more teachable than explaining “timeline gives turns, records gives messages inside a turn.”\\n\\nSo the minimal command set I’d teach is:\\n\\n```bash\\nbut agent sessions [branch <branch> | review <review> | change <change>] [--limit N]\\nbut agent show <session-id> [--turn <turn-id>] [--from end] [--limit N]\\n```\\n\\nDefault `show <session-id>` should return the recent timeline plus enough summary to pick a turn. Default `show --turn` should read from `end`, because catch-up usually means “what happened most recently?”\\n\\n**Naming**\\n\\nUse `session-id` and `turn-id`, not `session-key` / `turn-key`. “Key” sounds internal. Agents and humans understand IDs.\\n\\nI’d avoid `records` unless the underlying data is truly record-shaped. “Records” is vague. If you keep three commands, rename it:\\n\\n```bash\\nbut agent turns <session-id>\\nbut agent messages <session-id> --turn <turn-id>\\n```\\n\\nBut I still prefer `show`.\\n\\n**Misuse risks**\\n\\n`--from start` as a default is a trap. Long sessions will burn tokens and teach agents to read history chronologically when they usually need recency first.\\n\\nSet defaults like:\\n\\n```bash\\n--limit 20\\n--from end\\n```\\n\\nFor session listing, sort newest first. For timeline, sort oldest-to-newest only if limited output includes `has_more_before`; otherwise newest first is better for catch-up.\\n\\n**JSON fields**\\n\\nFor `sessions`:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"sessions\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"id\\\": \\\"sess_abc\\\",\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"Fix auth race in desktop\\\",\\n      \\\"scope\\\": {\\n        \\\"branch\\\": \\\"kb/auth-race\\\",\\n        \\\"review\\\": null,\\n        \\\"change\\\": \\\"chg_123\\\"\\n      },\\n      \\\"status\\\": \\\"active\\\",\\n      \\\"started_at\\\": \\\"2026-05-20T09:12:00-07:00\\\",\\n      \\\"updated_at\\\": \\\"2026-05-20T10:44:00-07:00\\\",\\n      \\\"turn_count\\\": 8,\\n      \\\"record_count\\\": 143,\\n      \\\"last_turn_id\\\": \\\"turn_008\\\",\\n      \\\"last_user_request\\\": \\\"Can you add the regression test?\\\",\\n      \\\"summary\\\": \\\"Investigated auth startup race, patched token refresh ordering, tests still failing in lite auth suite.\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"next_cursor\\\": null\\n}\\n```\\n\\nFor `show <session-id>`:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"session\\\": {\\n    \\\"id\\\": \\\"sess_abc\\\",\\n    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Fix auth race in desktop\\\",\\n    \\\"status\\\": \\\"active\\\",\\n    \\\"updated_at\\\": \\\"2026-05-20T10:44:00-07:00\\\",\\n    \\\"summary\\\": \\\"Current state in one useful paragraph.\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"turns\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"id\\\": \\\"turn_008\\\",\\n      \\\"index\\\": 8,\\n      \\\"started_at\\\": \\\"2026-05-20T10:31:00-07:00\\\",\\n      \\\"user_request\\\": \\\"Can you add the regression test?\\\",\\n      \\\"assistant_summary\\\": \\\"Added test scaffold but hit failing setup import.\\\",\\n      \\\"outcome\\\": \\\"blocked\\\",\\n      \\\"files_touched\\\": [\\n        \\\"crates/gitbutler-auth/src/refresh.rs\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"commands_run\\\": [\\n        \\\"cargo test -p gitbutler-auth\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"record_count\\\": 21,\\n      \\\"has_records\\\": true\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"pagination\\\": {\\n    \\\"limit\\\": 20,\\n    \\\"has_more_before\\\": true,\\n    \\\"has_more_after\\\": false\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nFor `show <session-id> --turn <turn-id>`:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"sess_abc\\\",\\n  \\\"turn\\\": {\\n    \\\"id\\\": \\\"turn_008\\\",\\n    \\\"index\\\": 8,\\n    \\\"user_request\\\": \\\"Can you add the regression test?\\\",\\n    \\\"summary\\\": \\\"Added test scaffold but hit failing setup import.\\\",\\n    \\\"outcome\\\": \\\"blocked\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"records\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"index\\\": 122,\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"assistant_message\\\",\\n      \\\"role\\\": \\\"assistant\\\",\\n      \\\"created_at\\\": \\\"2026-05-20T10:35:12-07:00\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"I’m checking the existing auth test pattern first.\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"index\\\": 123,\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"tool_call\\\",\\n      \\\"tool\\\": \\\"exec_command\\\",\\n      \\\"command\\\": \\\"rg \\\\\\\"refresh\\\\\\\" crates/gitbutler-auth\\\",\\n      \\\"status\\\": \\\"success\\\",\\n      \\\"summary\\\": \\\"Found refresh tests in refresh_tests.rs.\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"pagination\\\": {\\n    \\\"from\\\": \\\"end\\\",\\n    \\\"limit\\\": 20,\\n    \\\"has_more_before\\\": true,\\n    \\\"has_more_after\\\": false,\\n    \\\"next_from\\\": 102\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe killer fields are `summary`, `last_user_request`, `outcome`, `files_touched`, `commands_run`, `has_more_before`, and stable `index`. Those make agent catch-up obvious without forcing a full transcript read.\\n\\nFinal take: the current API is workable, but `sessions + show` is simpler, harder to misuse, and easier to teach.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:45:36.294Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}